03:46:25,840 --> 03:46:28,400
'I've just come back from the trial.

2635
03:46:28,399 --> 03:46:31,879
They brought in a verdict of guilty, of course.

2636
03:46:31,880 --> 03:46:34,720
But Miss Gilchrist is happy, you know.

2637
03:46:34,720 --> 03:46:41,280
She spends most of her time making 
plans to run a chain of tearooms.'

2638
03:46:41,279 --> 03:46:48,759
'Some people might think that she was 
always a little mad,' said Poirot.

2639
03:46:48,760 --> 03:46:53,120
'But me, I think not.'

2640
03:46:53,120 --> 03:46:55,479
'Goodness me, no, Poirot!

2641
03:46:55,479 --> 03:47:03,679
She was as sane as you and I when she planned 
Cora's murder and carried it out in cold blood.'

2642
03:47:03,680 --> 03:47:07,159
Poirot gave a little shiver.

2643
03:47:07,159 --> 03:47:15,120
'I am thinking,' he said, 'of some words 
that Susan Banks said - that she had  

2644
03:47:15,120 --> 03:47:20,840
never imagined a ladylike murderer.'

2645
03:47:20,840 --> 03:47:24,360
'Why not?' said Mr Entwhistle.

2646
03:47:24,359 --> 03:47:28,839
'It takes all sorts.'

2647
03:47:28,840 --> 03:47:34,000
They were silent - and Poirot 
thought of murderers he had known.

